{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"50a23372-cd93-468d-bb8f-87f96f5c2cc4","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2**, which supports constructor injection for `TestContext`. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests : IAsyncInitialization, IAsyncCleanup\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n\n    // Synchronous init via constructor injection\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        // other sync setup here\n    }\n\n    // Async init (replaces [TestInitialize] for async work)\n    public Task InitializeAsync()\n    {\n        // await async setup here\n        return Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    // Async cleanup (replaces [TestCleanup] for async work)\n    public Task CleanupAsync()\n    {\n        // await async teardown here\n        return Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void ExampleTest()\n    {\n        Assert.IsNotNull(_testContext);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **Constructor injection** — MSTest 3.x injects `TestContext` automatically via the constructor (no need for the old `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property).\n- **`IAsyncInitialization`** — implement this for async per-test setup (runs after the constructor).\n- **`IAsyncCleanup`** — implement this for async per-test teardown.\n- You can still use `[ClassInitialize]` / `[ClassCleanup]` for one-time class-level setup if needed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"83395c17-7386-4bdd-b6e8-0be7c4296e89","outputTokens":383,"requestId":"57C3:323C85:2DEE10A:30C6C85:6A0494D3"},"id":"69ffe82c-04d8-44cd-83ed-33b9c4f2bbdc","timestamp":"2026-05-13T15:12:29.274Z","parentId":"714d8bf8-63fb-4d02-80e4-b3760c52b1a8"}
